    <item>
      <title>IaaC | Pulumi | libvirt-python 01 | bootstrap</title>
      <link>/posts/2022-06-18-pulumi_libvirt-01_bootstrap/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 18 Jun 2022 00:00:00 +0900</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/posts/2022-06-18-pulumi_libvirt-01_bootstrap/</guid>
      <description>description Following my previous post about qemu/kvm setup, this is about pulumi/libvirt provider.
tasks  install pulumi bootstrap project test  1. install pulumi  https://pulumi.com/docs/reference/install/  curl -fsSL https://get.pulumi.com | sh source ~/.bashrc pulumi version  # personal aliases echo &amp;#39;alias pp=&amp;#34;pulumi up -y&amp;#34;&amp;#39; &amp;gt;&amp;gt; ~/.bashrc echo &amp;#39;alias pd=&amp;#34;pulumi destroy -y&amp;#34;&amp;#39; &amp;gt;&amp;gt; ~/.bashrc source ~/.bashrc 2. bootstrap project 1. state, local PROJECT_NAME=kvm-deb-02 PULUMI_ROOT=~/PULUMI PULUMI_STATE=${PULUMI_ROOT}/state/state-${PROJECT_NAME}  rm -rf ${PULUMI_ROOT}/${PROJECT_NAME} ${PULUMI_STATE} mkdir -p ${PULUMI_ROOT}/${PROJECT_NAME} cd ${PULUMI_ROOT}/${PROJECT_NAME} mkdir ${PULUMI_STATE} pulumi login file://${PULUMI_STATE} 2.</description>
      <content>&lt;h2 id=&#34;description&#34;&gt;description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following my previous post about qemu/kvm setup, this is about pulumi/libvirt provider.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;tasks&#34;&gt;tasks&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;install pulumi&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;bootstrap project&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;test&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;1-install-pulumi&#34;&gt;1. install pulumi&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://pulumi.com/docs/reference/install/&#34;&gt;https://pulumi.com/docs/reference/install/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#272822;background-color:#fafafa;-moz-tab-size:2;-o-tab-size:2;tab-size:2;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;curl -fsSL https://get.pulumi.com &lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; sh
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;source&lt;/span&gt; ~/.bashrc
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;pulumi version
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# personal aliases&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;alias pp=&amp;#34;pulumi up -y&amp;#34;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;      &amp;gt;&amp;gt; ~/.bashrc
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;alias pd=&amp;#34;pulumi destroy -y&amp;#34;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &amp;gt;&amp;gt; ~/.bashrc
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;source&lt;/span&gt; ~/.bashrc
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;2-bootstrap-project&#34;&gt;2. bootstrap project&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;1-state-local&#34;&gt;1. state, local&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#272822;background-color:#fafafa;-moz-tab-size:2;-o-tab-size:2;tab-size:2;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;PROJECT_NAME&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;kvm-deb-02
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;PULUMI_ROOT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;~/PULUMI
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;PULUMI_STATE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;PULUMI_ROOT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;/state/state-&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;PROJECT_NAME&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rm -rf &lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;PULUMI_ROOT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;/&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;PROJECT_NAME&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;PULUMI_STATE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;mkdir -p            &lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;PULUMI_ROOT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;/&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;PROJECT_NAME&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;cd&lt;/span&gt;                  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;PULUMI_ROOT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;/&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;PROJECT_NAME&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;mkdir               &lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;PULUMI_STATE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;pulumi login file://&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;PULUMI_STATE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;2-start-project&#34;&gt;2. start project&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#272822;background-color:#fafafa;-moz-tab-size:2;-o-tab-size:2;tab-size:2;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;pulumi new python &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8045ff&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8045ff&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;  --description &lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Creates a Ubuntu 20.04 VM via libvirt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8045ff&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8045ff&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;  --name &lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;PROJECT_NAME&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8045ff&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8045ff&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;  --stack dev
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;source&lt;/span&gt; venv/bin/activate
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;export&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;PULUMI_CONFIG_PASSPHRASE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;pip install pulumi_libvirt
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#272822;background-color:#fafafa;-moz-tab-size:2;-o-tab-size:2;tab-size:2;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;KVM_HOST=kvm-deb-02
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;ssh-copy-id root@${KVM_HOST}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;pulumi config set libvirt:uri qemu+ssh://root@${KVM_HOST}/system
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;This will create a &lt;code&gt;dummy&lt;/code&gt; virtual machine, main purpose is to confirm that communication is working fine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;3-test&#34;&gt;3. test&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;in my &lt;code&gt;hypervisor&lt;/code&gt;, run:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#272822;background-color:#fafafa;-moz-tab-size:2;-o-tab-size:2;tab-size:2;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;watch virsh list --all
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;and in my &lt;code&gt;workstation&lt;/code&gt;, run:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#272822;background-color:#fafafa;-moz-tab-size:2;-o-tab-size:2;tab-size:2;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;pulumi up
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;then check output of both terminals, then destroy it&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#272822;background-color:#fafafa;-moz-tab-size:2;-o-tab-size:2;tab-size:2;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;pulumi destroy
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Virtualization | qemu/kvm/libvirt | my qemu/kvm/libvirt setup</title>
      <link>/posts/2022-06-16-my_qemu-kvm-libvirt_setup/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 16 Jun 2022 00:00:00 +0900</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/posts/2022-06-16-my_qemu-kvm-libvirt_setup/</guid>
      <description>description I will create multiple content related to qemu/kvm/libvirt, then this post is to use as reference.
tasks  install OS (using debian netinstall) install virtualization tools modify main network to use as bridge  1. install OS (using debian netinstall)  I usually go with fedora server but, I need different distribution because there is an error with ssh and Terraform+Pulumi. Ubuntu is using netplan (+ snap) and I just need a hypervisor, then debian is my choice  2.</description>
      <content>&lt;h2 id=&#34;description&#34;&gt;description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I will create multiple content related to qemu/kvm/libvirt, then this post is to use as reference.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;tasks&#34;&gt;tasks&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;install OS (using debian netinstall)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;install virtualization tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;modify main network to use as bridge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;1-install-os-using-debian-netinstall&#34;&gt;1. install OS (using debian netinstall)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;I usually go with fedora server but, I need different distribution because there is an error with ssh and Terraform+Pulumi.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ubuntu is using netplan (+ snap) and I just need a &lt;code&gt;hypervisor&lt;/code&gt;, then debian is my choice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;2-install-virtualization-tools&#34;&gt;2. install virtualization tools&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#272822;background-color:#fafafa;-moz-tab-size:2;-o-tab-size:2;tab-size:2;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;cat /proc/cpuinfo &lt;span style=&#34;color:#111&#34;&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;grep -E &lt;span style=&#34;color:#d88200&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;vmx|svm&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#272822;background-color:#fafafa;-moz-tab-size:2;-o-tab-size:2;tab-size:2;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;apt install qemu-kvm libvirt-daemon-system cockpit cockpit-machines
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;reboot
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;3-modify-main-network-to-use-as-bridge&#34;&gt;3. modify main network to use as bridge&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linuxconfig.org/how-to-use-bridged-networking-with-libvirt-and-kvm&#34;&gt;https://linuxconfig.org/how-to-use-bridged-networking-with-libvirt-and-kvm&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#272822;background-color:#fafafa;-moz-tab-size:2;-o-tab-size:2;tab-size:2;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;apt-get install bridge-utils -y
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#272822;background-color:#fafafa;-moz-tab-size:2;-o-tab-size:2;tab-size:2;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;cp -a /etc/network/interfaces ~/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;vi /etc/network/interfaces
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#272822;background-color:#fafafa;-moz-tab-size:2;-o-tab-size:2;tab-size:2;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# This file describes the network interfaces available on your system&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# and how to activate them. For more information, see interfaces(5).&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# The loopback network interface&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;auto lo
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;iface lo inet loopback
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# Specify that the physical interface that should be connected to the bridge&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# should be configured manually, to avoid conflicts with NetworkManager&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;iface enp1s0 inet manual
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# The br0 bridge settings&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;auto br0
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;iface br0 inet static
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  bridge_ports enp1s0
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    address 192.168.1.207
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    broadcast 192.168.1.255
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    netmask 255.255.255.0
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    gateway 192.168.1.1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;#optional&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    bridge_stp off
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    bridge_fd &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    bridge_maxwait &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
